			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Softened Water</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">软化水</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Soft Water</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Soft Water</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Water</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<CASNumber>7732-18-5</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Softened water is the result of a process of removing the dissolved calcium and magnesium salts that cause hardness in water. It does not form insoluble scale or precipitates in pipes and tanks or interfere with cleaners such as soap. It is indispensable in many industries and is common in homes with hard water. While it is fine for bathing, it is recommended to use distilled water for drinking or cooking. Sodium bicarbonate, also known as washing soda or baking soda, reacts with hardness minerals and softens water.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">软化水是去除造成水硬度的溶解钙盐和镁盐的过程。它不会在管道和水箱中形成不溶性水垢或沉淀物，也不会干扰肥皂等清洁剂。它在许多行业都不可或缺，在硬水家庭中也很常见。虽然它可以用来洗澡，但建议使用蒸馏水来饮用或做饭。碳酸氢钠，又称洗衣粉或小苏打，可与硬度较高的矿物质发生反应，软化水质。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>H2O</sumFormula>
